messages.msgSnippet: I have seen a few pics of you, Sandra,  on your web site, in HEM.   But you know what is in my mind when I picture you ? The picture on the front of   The
messages.messageBody:
I have seen a few pics of you, Sandra, on your web site, in HEM. But you know what is in my mind when I picture you ?
The picture on the front of The Continuum Concept. The mom holding the baby. It must resemble you in a way. I don't know?

Funny huh? I thought you might like that, its such a nice, calm picture.

Kelli

messages.subject: What Sandra looks like
messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 3/26/2003 9:59:36 AM Eastern Standard Time, ... Never pictured you as tall and blonde. I actually thought it was cool when I saw a picture
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 3/26/2003 9:59:36 AM Eastern Standard Time,
AlwaysLearning@yahoogroups.com writes:

> Too many times to count, when people have met me they look at me like I'm an
>
> imposter and say "I thought you would be tall. And blonde." I must write
>
> tall and blonde. If it had only happened one or two times, I'd think it
> was
> just that one person saw a movie or something... <g>
>

Never pictured you as tall and blonde. I actually thought it was cool when I
saw a picture of you (and then, in person, although I hadn't pictured you
grimacing in pain) that you looked exactly like I imagined. (And that's a
good thing)
Kathryn
